<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Peer on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/peer/</link><description>Recent content in Peer on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/peer/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C Connection reset by peer: ECONNRESET</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/connection-reset/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/connection-reset/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="connection-reset-by-peer-econnreset"&gt;Connection reset by peer: ECONNRESET&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ECONNRESET occurs when the remote end of a connection abruptly closes it (sends a RST packet) while data is being transferred.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Server crashed
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;send&lt;/span&gt;(sock, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;data&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;4&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// server process died
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Server closed connection
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Server called close() on socket
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Firewall RST
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Firewall injecting RST packet
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-handle-gracefully"&gt;Fix 1: Handle gracefully&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ssize_t&lt;/span&gt; result &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;recv&lt;/span&gt;(sock, buf, size, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (result &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; errno &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; ECONNRESET) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fprintf&lt;/span&gt;(stderr, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Connection reset by peer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;close&lt;/span&gt;(sock);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-keepalive"&gt;Fix 2: Use keepalive&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; opt &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setsockopt&lt;/span&gt;(sock, SOL_SOCKET, SO_KEEPALIVE, &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;opt, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(opt));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-implement-reconnection"&gt;Fix 3: Implement reconnection&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; i &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;; i &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;; i&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;++&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;connect&lt;/span&gt;(sock, (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;struct&lt;/span&gt; sockaddr&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;addr, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(addr)) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;break&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;sleep&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/broken-pipe/"&gt;Broken pipe&lt;/a&gt; — EPIPE.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/connection-refused-c/"&gt;Connection refused&lt;/a&gt; — ECONNREFUSED.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/operation-timed-out/"&gt;Connection timed out&lt;/a&gt; — ETIMEDOUT.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Linux ECONNRESET (errno 68) — Connection Reset by Peer Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/errno-68/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/errno-68/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="linux-econnreset-errno-68--connection-reset-by-peer"&gt;Linux ECONNRESET (errno 68) — Connection Reset by Peer&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ECONNRESET (errno 68) means the remote peer forcibly closed the connection. This error occurs when the remote side sends a TCP RST packet, indicating it has terminated the connection unexpectedly. It is distinct from ECONNABORTED (errno 67) because ECONNRESET is triggered by the remote peer, not the local machine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remote server crashed or restarted unexpectedly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remote application closed the connection prematurely&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Network device sent a reset (firewall, NAT, load balancer)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remote process ran out of resources&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix-econnreset"&gt;How to Fix ECONNRESET&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-check-server-status"&gt;1. Check Server Status&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Verify the remote server is running:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] npm Peer Dependency Error — ERESOLVE unable to resolve</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/npm/npm-peer/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/npm/npm-peer/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;An ERESOLVE error occurs when npm cannot automatically resolve peer dependency conflicts. Two packages require incompatible versions of the same dependency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Packages require different major versions of a shared dependency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outdated lock file with stale dependency tree&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;npm v7+ enforces strict peer dependency resolution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Circular or conflicting dependency requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="use-legacy-peer-dependencies"&gt;Use Legacy Peer Dependencies&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;npm install --legacy-peer-deps
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="force-installation"&gt;Force Installation&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;npm install --force
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="use-npm-overrides"&gt;Use npm Overrides&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-json" data-lang="json"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;{
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;#34;overrides&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;#34;package-a&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;#34;shared-dep&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;^2.0.0&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="delete-node_modules-and-reinstall"&gt;Delete node_modules and Reinstall&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;rm -rf node_modules package-lock.json
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;npm install --legacy-peer-deps
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="pin-specific-package-version"&gt;Pin Specific Package Version&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;npm install shared-dep@2.0.0
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 1: React version conflict&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;npm install react-datepicker
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# ERESOLVE unable to resolve dependency tree&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Fix: npm install react-datepicker --legacy-peer-deps&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 2: Clear and reinstall&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;rm -rf node_modules package-lock.json
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;npm install --legacy-peer-deps
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/npm/npm-audit/"&gt;npm Audit&lt;/a&gt; — security vulnerabilities found&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/npm/npm-version/"&gt;npm Version Error&lt;/a&gt; — version conflict error&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Connection Reset — Connection Reset by Peer</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/connection-reset/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/connection-reset/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="connection-reset--connection-reset-by-peer"&gt;Connection Reset — Connection Reset by Peer&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An IO error with the message &amp;ldquo;Connection reset by peer (os error 104)&amp;rdquo; occurs when the remote side of a TCP connection sends a RST packet, abruptly closing the connection.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A connection reset happens when:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The server process crashes or is killed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The server&amp;rsquo;s OS closes the connection abruptly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A firewall or load balancer drops the connection.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Network issues cause the connection to become invalid.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unlike &amp;ldquo;connection refused&amp;rdquo; (which means the server isn&amp;rsquo;t listening), &amp;ldquo;connection reset&amp;rdquo; means a connection was established but then forcibly closed. The error code is 104 (&lt;code&gt;ECONNRESET&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Connection Reset — Peer Reset Connection</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/connection-reset-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/connection-reset-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="connection-reset--peer-reset-connection"&gt;Connection Reset — Peer Reset Connection&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An IO error with the message &amp;ldquo;Connection reset by peer (os error 104)&amp;rdquo; occurs when the remote end of an established TCP connection sends a RST packet, forcibly closing it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A connection reset means a connection &lt;em&gt;was&lt;/em&gt; established but was then abruptly terminated. The peer (server or client) sent a TCP RST instead of a graceful FIN. Error code 104 (&lt;code&gt;ECONNRESET&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common scenarios:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>